<h2 class="secondary-homepage-header-left-2" style="margin-top: 0px;">Victor Hruby Symposium</h2>
<a href="https://victorhruby.com/" target="_blank"><img src="https://americanpeptidesociety.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/hruby_victor_symposium.jpg" alt="Victor Hruby Symposium" class="img-responsive" style="margin-bottom: 11px;"/></a>
<p>The American Peptide Society invites all members and colleagues to attend the <strong>Victor J. Hruby Symposium</strong>, May&nbsp;21–22,&nbsp;2026, in Tucson, Arizona. This landmark event honors Victor, founding APS President and one of the most influential figures in modern peptide chemistry. Over more than five decades, His discoveries have shaped our understanding of peptide structure, signaling, and drug design, while his mentorship has inspired generations of scientists worldwide. Join us in celebrating his extraordinary legacy and the future of peptide innovation.</p>
